etsysStationLocationMIB.name: etsysStationLocationMIB

revisions.description: Added etsysPublishLocationUserId and etsysPublishLocationPassword to etsysPublishLocationURLTable.

Added location batch report to provide a way for consumer programs to receive the list of the locations of all associated stations. Added etsysLocationEngineTrackAreaChange to etsysLocationConfiguration.
The initial version of this MIB module.

etsysStationLocationMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Extreme Networks, Inc. 145 Rio Robles San Jose, CA 95134 USA Phone: +1 408 579-2800 E-mail: support@extremenetworks.com WWW: http://www.extremenetworks.com
etsysStationLocationMIB.description: This MIB provides an interface to manage the wireless station localization application. It allows configuration of the application as well retrieving information about location of managed Station that are associated to controller or are configured to be tracked even without being associated.

FloorEnvironmentType.name: FloorEnvironmentType
FloorEnvironmentType.description: Type of indoor construction materials used on its floor. openSpace(0): Indoor open space (halls, auditoriums) lightDivision(1): Office environment with light divisions (cubicles) dryWallsDivision(2): Office environment with dry walls divisions hardDivision(3): Office Environment with hard divisions (brick) interiorWalls(4): Interior Walls (need be defined in the floor plan)

etsysLocationEngineEnable.name: etsysLocationEngineEnable
etsysLocationEngineEnable.description: Setting this value to true (1), enables the location engine to track stations, otherwise no station will be tracked.

etsysLocationEngineAutoTrkEnable.name: etsysLocationEngineAutoTrkEnable
etsysLocationEngineAutoTrkEnable.description: If this variable is set to true and etsysLocationEngineEnable is set to true then all associated stations will be tracked up to the platform limit for location tracking.

etsysLocationEngineGlblAPHeight.name: etsysLocationEngineGlblAPHeight
etsysLocationEngineGlblAPHeight.description: Default height of access point to be used if the floor configuration has not provided any height for any AP servicing the floor. The range of height is 0 to 1000 in centimeters.

etsysLocationEngineGlobalEnv.name: etsysLocationEngineGlobalEnv
etsysLocationEngineGlobalEnv.description: Type of indoor construction materials assumed when the floor plan does not specify the primary construction materials used on its floor.

etsysLocationMaxFloorLimit.name: etsysLocationMaxFloorLimit
etsysLocationMaxFloorLimit.description: The maximum number of floor plan files that can be stored and used on this controller.

etsysLocationFloorConfigured.name: etsysLocationFloorConfigured
etsysLocationFloorConfigured.description: The number of floors that have been configured and currently used.

etsysFloorTable.name: etsysFloorTable
etsysFloorTable.description: A table that describes attributes of floors configured for use by the Location Engine.

etsysFloorEntry.name: etsysFloorEntry
etsysFloorEntry.description: An entry describing a single floor in the location engine's database.

etsysFloorID.name: etsysFloorID
etsysFloorID.description: Floor ID associated to the floor. This index ranges from one to etsysLocationMaxFloorLimit. This ID persists over reboots and upgrades.

etsysFloorRowStatus.name: etsysFloorRowStatus
etsysFloorRowStatus.description: RowStatus of the entry, though currently only deletion is allowed for this field.

etsysFloorName.name: etsysFloorName
etsysFloorName.description: Textual string identifying floor name. Supports UTF-8 character set, except Double Quotes and ASCII control characters.

etsysFloorNumberOfAPs.name: etsysFloorNumberOfAPs
etsysFloorNumberOfAPs.description: Number of access point have been assigned to this floor to track stations on this floor.

etsysFloorWidth.name: etsysFloorWidth
etsysFloorWidth.description: Width of the floor in centimeters.

etsysFloorLength.name: etsysFloorLength
etsysFloorLength.description: Length of the floor in centimeters.

etsysFloorNumberOfCells.name: etsysFloorNumberOfCells
etsysFloorNumberOfCells.description: Number of cells on this floor.

etsysFloorCellWidth.name: etsysFloorCellWidth
etsysFloorCellWidth.description: Width of each cell for this floor in centimeters.

etsysFloorCellLength.name: etsysFloorCellLength
etsysFloorCellLength.description: Length of each cell for this floor in centimeters.

etsysFloorEnvironment.name: etsysFloorEnvironment
etsysFloorEnvironment.description: Type of propagation model for the floor.

etsysFloorHashString.name: etsysFloorHashString
etsysFloorHashString.description: MD5 hash of the file as received during download.

etsysMaxTrackedStationLimit.name: etsysMaxTrackedStationLimit
etsysMaxTrackedStationLimit.description: Maximum number of stations that this platform can track. Stations are tracked on the basis of either being associated to the controller or administratively added to the 'On-Demand Tracking' list

etsysMaxOnDemandStationLimit.name: etsysMaxOnDemandStationLimit
etsysMaxOnDemandStationLimit.description: Maximum number of stations that can be configured to be tracked as on-demand basis.

etsysOnDemandStationTable.name: etsysOnDemandStationTable
etsysOnDemandStationTable.description: A list of stations to be tracked by the Location Engine. Location tracking of a station may stop when it is removed from the list. The list is configured by the administrator and is used to reserve capacity to ensure that the addresses in the list are among those tracked by the location engine.

etsysOnDemandStationEntry.name: etsysOnDemandStationEntry
etsysOnDemandStationEntry.description: The address of a single station to be tracked.

etsysOnDemandStationMAC.name: etsysOnDemandStationMAC
etsysOnDemandStationMAC.description: MAC address of the station to be tracked.

etsysLocationEngineTrackAreaChange.name: etsysLocationEngineTrackAreaChange
etsysLocationEngineTrackAreaChange.description: Setting this value to enable(1), the location engine will track the area changes, otherwise, the area information is determined by the associated AP.

etsysLocationEngineTrackMode.name: etsysLocationEngineTrackMode
etsysLocationEngineTrackMode.description: trackClients(1) : All associated stations will be tracked up to the platform limit. trackAll(2) : All Mac address will be tracked up to the platform limit. trackNone(3) : Location engine is tracking the on demand list only.

etsysTrackedStationTable.name: etsysTrackedStationTable
etsysTrackedStationTable.description: Table containing information about tracked stations.

etsysTrackedStationEntry.name: etsysTrackedStationEntry
etsysTrackedStationEntry.description: An entry describing the location of one tracked station.

etsysTrackedStationMAC.name: etsysTrackedStationMAC
etsysTrackedStationMAC.description: MAC address associated to the station that is being tracked.

etsysTrackedStationFloorID.name: etsysTrackedStationFloorID
etsysTrackedStationFloorID.description: The ID of the floor on which the station appears to be active.

etsysTrackedStationLocationType.name: etsysTrackedStationLocationType
etsysTrackedStationLocationType.description: This object identifies the type of location report for the station. The meaning of other fields in this table and the etsysLocationGridTable depend on the value of this object. If this object has a value of 'cellOfOrigin' then etsysStationLocnGridX and etsysStationLocationGridY will be set to -1 in the etsysStationLocationGridTable entry for this station.

etsysTrackedStationReportingAPSN.name: etsysTrackedStationReportingAPSN
etsysTrackedStationReportingAPSN.description: The serial number of the access point that reported an RSS value for the station. This object is meaningful only when the value of etsysTrackedStationLocationType is cellOfOrigin. The cell of origin method determines location based on the probable distance of the subject from a known location, in this case, the location of the AP that reported the RSS value. Cell of Origin is used when fewer than three APs report seeing the station at one time. If two APs report the station then the serial number of the AP reporting the strongest RSS is reported as the station's etsysTrackedStationReportingAPSN.

etsysTrackedStationAPDistance.name: etsysTrackedStationAPDistance
etsysTrackedStationAPDistance.description: The distance (in meters) of the station from the access point with the serial number in etsysTrackedStationReportingAPSN. This object is meaningful only when the value of etsysTrackedStationLocationType is cellOfOrigin.

etsysStationLocationGridTable.name: etsysStationLocationGridTable
etsysStationLocationGridTable.description: When the location type is rssBasedLocation it is likely that there will be a number of probable locations calculated for one station. This table lists the most recently rssBasedLocation-calculated probable locations of each tracked station. Each row of the table represents one probable location of one tracked station. The table is indexed by the subject station's MAC address and an internal identifier for the cell described by the entry. The cell is a cell on the floor identified by the etsysTrackedStationFloorID object in the etsysTrackedStationEntry for the subject station.

etsysStationLocationGridEntry.name: etsysStationLocationGridEntry
etsysStationLocationGridEntry.description: One entry in this table providing one of the possible location for the station with associated probability.

etsysStationLocnGridIndex.name: etsysStationLocnGridIndex
etsysStationLocnGridIndex.description: Internally assigned number to those location starting from one to the maximum number of reported locations. This field has no meaning by itself.

etsysStationLocnGridX.name: etsysStationLocnGridX
etsysStationLocnGridX.description: X-coordinate associated to the location of the reported cell.

etsysStationLocnGridY.name: etsysStationLocnGridY
etsysStationLocnGridY.description: Y-coordinate associated to the location of the reported cell.

etsysStationLocnGridProbability.name: etsysStationLocnGridProbability
etsysStationLocnGridProbability.description: Estimated percentage chance that the station is actually located in the identified cell. A value of zero means the location is not known.

etsysLocationBatchReportEnable.name: etsysLocationBatchReportEnable
etsysLocationBatchReportEnable.description: Setting this value to true (1) enables the location batch reporting feature.

etsysLocationBatchReportFrequency.name: etsysLocationBatchReportFrequency
etsysLocationBatchReportFrequency.description: The report frequency setting in seconds. Currently 60, 120, 300, 600, 1200, 1800, 3600, 7200 and 14400 seconds are supported. Other values are un-supported and will be rejected.

etsysPublishLocationURLMaxEntries.name: etsysPublishLocationURLMaxEntries
etsysPublishLocationURLMaxEntries.description: Maximum number of URLs supported by the controller.

etsysPublishLocationURLNumEntries.name: etsysPublishLocationURLNumEntries
etsysPublishLocationURLNumEntries.description: The current number of entries in the etsysPublishLocationURLTable.

etsysPublishLocationURLTable.name: etsysPublishLocationURLTable
etsysPublishLocationURLTable.description: Table containing destination URLs to which the controller posts location information. Only http and https are supported.

etsysPublishLocationURLEntry.name: etsysPublishLocationURLEntry
etsysPublishLocationURLEntry.description: An entry describing the destination URL.

etsysPublishLocationIndex.name: etsysPublishLocationIndex
etsysPublishLocationIndex.description: The index for a configured destination URL.

etsysPublishLocationURL.name: etsysPublishLocationURL
etsysPublishLocationURL.description: The URL of the destination to which a report is pushed.

etsysPublishLocationRowStatus.name: etsysPublishLocationRowStatus
etsysPublishLocationRowStatus.description: A control that will allow one entry to be added, activated, deactivated, or removed from the table.

etsysPublishLocationUserId.name: etsysPublishLocationUserId
etsysPublishLocationUserId.description: The login name for the destination URL server.

etsysPublishLocationPassword.name: etsysPublishLocationPassword
etsysPublishLocationPassword.description: The password for the destination URL server. On a read, a dummy (not real password) will be returned.

etsysLocationBatchReportDimensionUnit.name: etsysLocationBatchReportDimensionUnit
etsysLocationBatchReportDimensionUnit.description: The units for reported x and y location coordinates.

etsysFloorGroup.description: List of objects that defines attributes of a configured floor.

etsysOnDemandStationsGroup.description: List of objects that define attribute of a on-demand stations to be tracked.

etsysTrackedStationsGroup.description: List of objects that define a tracked stations attributes.

etsysLocationBatchReportGroup.name: etsysLocationBatchReportGroup

etsysLocationEngineGlobalGroup2.name: etsysLocationEngineGlobalGroup2
etsysLocationEngineGlobalGroup2.description: Objects defining configuration attributes of a location tracking components.

etsysLocationEngineGlobalGroup3.description: Objects defining configuration attributes of a location tracking components.

etsysStationLocationCompliance.description: This group is mandatory for all devices that support reporting and configuration of station location.
